# To find all html tags in string using Regular expression in JS

const text = `hello <h1 style="color:red;" class="hello"> and <span style="color:red;">good</span> hello </h1> bad <p>hello</p>
<br/>
<hr />
<bala> hello </bala></bala>`;


Regular expression: /(<(?<first>\w+).*?>.*?<\/(\k<first>)>)|(<\w+\s?\/>)/g

Link: https://regex101.com/r/KiXjnu/2
